perl-IPC-DirQueue: perl-IPC-DirQueue (disk-based many-to-many queueing system)
perl-IPC-DirQueue:
perl-IPC-DirQueue: This module implements a FIFO queueing infrastructure, using a
perl-IPC-DirQueue: directory as the communications and storage media.  No daemon
perl-IPC-DirQueue: process is required to manage the queue; all communication takes
perl-IPC-DirQueue: place via the filesystem.
